683
00:46:03,873 --> 00:46:06,501
What are you doing, Sara?

684
00:46:06,576 --> 00:46:09,545
Honestly, Sara, I don't
understand you anymore, okay?

685
00:46:09,612 --> 00:46:12,206
Please, tell me something.

686
00:46:12,281 --> 00:46:15,250
Tell me anything that makes
just a little bit of sense.

687
00:46:16,752 --> 00:46:19,687
I've just spent
the entire flight...

688
00:46:19,755 --> 00:46:22,952
staring into the sky,
thinking.

689
00:46:23,025 --> 00:46:26,722
Not about my fiance,
but about this mystery guy...

690
00:46:26,796 --> 00:46:29,731
I met a million
and a half hours ago.

691
00:46:29,799 --> 00:46:33,235
A guy I don't even remember,
except for this...

692
00:46:33,302 --> 00:46:36,829
vague picture I have
inside my head.

693
00:46:36,906 --> 00:46:40,467
It was just a few seconds.
A fragment, really.

694
00:46:40,543 --> 00:46:43,137
And it was like...

695
00:46:43,212 --> 00:46:45,544
in that moment,

696
00:46:45,615 --> 00:46:49,073
the whole universe existed
just to bring us together.

697
00:46:50,453 --> 00:46:52,387
That's why I'm here.

698
00:46:52,455 --> 00:46:56,721
That's why I'm gonna let fate
take me wherever it wants to go.

699
00:46:56,792 --> 00:47:01,320
Because when all this is over,
at least I'm never gonna have
to think of him ever again.

700
00:47:02,932 --> 00:47:04,866
Let's just pray
he's a bald fascist...

701
00:47:04,934 --> 00:47:08,233
who picks his nose
and wipes it under the car seat.

702
00:47:13,743 --> 00:47:16,041
- Hi.
- Hi.

703
00:47:16,112 --> 00:47:18,012
Could you hold on?

704
00:47:32,695 --> 00:47:34,856
Where are you going?

705
00:47:34,931 --> 00:47:37,923
You better be buying me one
frigging big birthday cake,
that's all I gotta say.

706
00:47:38,000 --> 00:47:39,934
Could I get your
destination, please?

707
00:47:40,002 --> 00:47:43,836
- The Waldorf, I guess.
- Finally she gets it.

708
00:47:45,875 --> 00:47:49,538
Okay, we are going...
that way.

709
00:47:49,612 --> 00:47:51,876
And I'm gonna follow.

710
00:47:51,948 --> 00:47:54,883
You can do it yourself. Just open up
the computer and look into it.

711
00:47:54,951 --> 00:47:58,387
- I'm not even sure that I can
give you this information.
- If you can't, why can't you?

712
00:47:58,454 --> 00:48:00,945
Because I'm just a temp, okay?
I don't know the rules.

713
00:48:01,023 --> 00:48:03,457
Couple of months out of college,
you're acting like you're
part of the establishment.

714
00:48:03,526 --> 00:48:07,292
No, no, no, no, no--
What about privacy law, huh?

715
00:48:07,363 --> 00:48:09,797
Forget about privacy laws.
You know what privacy laws do?

716
00:48:09,865 --> 00:48:12,493
- No.
- They protect millionaires.
Do you know who those are?

717
00:48:12,568 --> 00:48:14,502
- Who?
- Tell him who they are.

718
00:48:14,570 --> 00:48:16,663
- Tell him.
- Kids your age.

719
00:48:16,739 --> 00:48:20,231
Pimple-faced college dropouts who
have made unhealthy sums of money...

720
00:48:20,309 --> 00:48:23,176
forming Internet companies
that create no concrete products,

721
00:48:23,246 --> 00:48:26,147
provide no viable services and still
manage to generate profits...

722
00:48:26,215 --> 00:48:28,809
for all of its lazy, day-trading,
son-of-a-bitch shareholders.

723
00:48:28,884 --> 00:48:32,251
Meanwhile, as a tortured member
of the disenfranchised proletariat,

724
00:48:32,321 --> 00:48:35,813
you find some altruistic need
to protect these digital
plantation owners?

725
00:48:35,891 --> 00:48:38,223
Wow. Come on.

726
00:48:41,831 --> 00:48:45,198
Come on.

